{
  "texts": [
    "As solar cells operate, they invariably generate heat.",
    "This heat can originate from multiple sources, including the absorbed sunlight, resistive losses in the cell's electrical contacts, and even environmental factors.",
    "The temperature of a solar cell can fluctuate widely based on its location, time of day, and exposure to sunlight (Dwivedi et al., 2020).",
    "The influence of temperature on solar cell performance is multifaceted and can have both positive and negative effects.",
    "Understanding these effects is crucial for optimizing the efficiency and longevity of photovoltaic systems."
  ]
}